Rating: 3
First time I attempted potato salad. This really is a good, solid recipe. The red skinned potatoes I used were too big, so I cooked them longer and ended up cutting the slices in half after cooking. I also added celery. I used lower fat mayo and sour cream, and it worked out fine... creamy with good flavor. Plus it was light.. not like heavy, drier potato salads that have eggs and bacon. And it was really easy to make.

Rating: 4
I have never been a traditional potato salad fan--too much mayo, icky eggs--it just wasn't for me. Have been looking for a great sour cream/mustard-based recipe forever, and found it in this one! Based on other reviews, I added about four stalks of finely-chopped celery, and used green spring onions. I also had two strips of leftover, cooked bacon from breakfast that I added. This will be my go-to potato recipe from now on! And steaming the potatoes in the microwave made this quick and easy to prepare!

