Rating: 4
I cut 9 red potatoes in 1/2 inch slices, and then cut each slice in half. then i boiled the potatoes in water with a LOT of salt added. i put the heat on medium high with only a slow slight boil for about 18-20 minutes until tender. drain and toss with distilled white vinegar and lemon juice. cooled them down in freezer for a few minutes. used food processor to separately dice parsley, 5 green onions and enough of dunbar's sweet roasted red peppers (12oz jar) to fill 1/2 cup. mix with helmann's light mayonnaise and sour cream (put 1/2 cup in instead of 1/4 cup to minimize the mayonnaise taste) and dijon mustard. peppers ended up being more pureed then diced, so i whisked them in with the above ingredients. once the potatoes have cooled to room temperature, i mixed the dressing in layer by layer with the potatoes and a tons of thinly chopped sweet celery (crescents). it is AWESOME! so delicious and worked perfectly! the potatoes are perfectly tender and not mushy and the peppers taste great! and i think the celery added a TON of extra crisp and tastes great. i would DEFINITELY make this recipe again, especially since i ate a ton of it right after it was done :)

