I only gave 3 forks because the salad REALLY needed some salt and pepper and some finely-minced celery to round out the flavor. I used Yukon Gold instead of red-skinned potatoes, as I prefer the waxier potato in a salad. They were wonderful steamed. The proportions of the dressing were perfect for a creamy salad, and I will definitely make it again. I didn't have roasted peppers, so I used fresh grape tomatoes, which gave a nice color and a burst of flavor that made the salad excellent.

