This is a delicious potato salad. I roasted my own red pepper (just one medium pepper was needed to get 1/2 cup chopped). I have finally figured out that the key to good potato salad is a good amount of salt in the potato water and then tossing the warm potatoes with some type of vinagrette before mixing with other ingredients. Yummy! I served this on mothers day and my mother-in-law went back for seconds and couldn't stop talking about it!

